@NODE "Multitask" "MultiTask."
@TOC "MAINE"

   @{B}@{FG SHINE}=====»@{FG TEXT} Multitask. @{FG SHINE}«=====@{FG TEXT}@{UB}

   You CAN multitask by pressing `LeftAmiga'+`a', and jump back to the
   program with the same keys.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Installation."
@TOC "MAINE"

   @{B}@{FG SHINE}=====»@{FG TEXT} Installation. @{FG SHINE}«=====@{FG TEXT}@{UB}

   @{B}HD Installation.@{UB}
   Copy the WonderWare-ModulePlayer (drawer) anywhere on your HD and copy
   AMOS.library and MEDPlayer.library to the Libs (drawer).

   @{B}Disk Installation.@{UB}
   If you use disks then you`ll have to format a disk and install a
   bootblock. You could type like this in CLI: Format DF0: . Then to install
   a bootblock, just type Install DF0: .(That`s not so hard to do, is it???)
   Then you`ll have to move the S (drawer), C (drawer) and LIBS (drawer) to
   the formatted disk.  The following things should be in the C (drawer):
   LoadWB
   EndCli
   The file Startup-Sequence should be in the S (drawer). (It follows with
   the archive) It should look like this:
   -------------------< CUT HERE >-------------------------
   LoadWB
   EndCli
   -------------------< CUT HERE >-------------------------
   Then you must copy the WonderWare-ModulePlayer (drawer) to the disk.
   After that you should reset your AMIGA and boot with your
   WonderWare-ModulePlayer disk. When the WB has been loaded just open the
   disk and then open the WonderWare-ModulePlayer (drawer) and then click on
   the WonderWare-ModulePlayer icon. It should start.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Main screen" "Main screen."
@TOC "MAINE"

   @{B}@{FG SHINE}=====»@{FG TEXT} Main screen. @{FG SHINE}«=====@{FG TEXT}@{UB}


   The top of the screen look like this:
    _______________________________________________________________________
   |     Load module      |  1 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |----------.-----------|  2 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |   Play   |   Stop    |  3 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |----------^-----------|  4 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |    Save settings     |  5 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |----------------------|  6 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |    Loop Off/On       |  7 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |----------------------|  8 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |@{"    Change palette    " LINK "Change palette screen"}|  9 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |----------.-----------| 10 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   | Register |  About    | 11 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |----------|-----------| 12 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |  Erase   | Erase all | 13 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |----------^-----------| 14 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |       E X I T        | 15 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   |----------------------| 16 |_____________________________________| MOD |
   :                      :    :                                     :     :
   .                      .    .                                     .     .

   @{B}Load Module    @{UB}- Opens a window and lets you load a module.
                    Before you load a module you must check that it stands
                    MOD at the right beside the right module if you should
                    load a MOD module, and it should be MED if you should
                    load a MED module.
   @{B}Play           @{UB}- Play the module that you loaded.
   @{B}Stop           @{UB}- Stops the music that plays.
   @{B}Save settings  @{UB}- Saves the settings, the palette and the modules.
                    NOT in UNREGISTERED version.
   @{B}Loop On/Off    @{UB}- Repeats the module On/Off. Only works on MOD
                    modules.
   @{B}Change Palette @{UB}- Change the colours.
   @{B}About          @{UB}- See about screen.
   @{B}Register       @{UB}- See register screen.
   @{B}Erase          @{UB}- Clear the active module.
   @{B}Erase all      @{UB}- Clear all modules.
   @{B}Exit           @{UB}- Exits the program.
   @{B}1-17           @{UB}- Changes which module is active.
   @{B}MOD            @{UB}- Shows what kind that module is, you must change this
                    before you load a module, change between MOD and MED by
                    pressing left mouse key.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Change palette screen" "Change palette screen."
@TOC "MAINE"

   @{B}@{FG SHINE}=====»@{FG TEXT} Change palette screen. @{FG SHINE}«=====@{FG TEXT}@{UB}

   The screen look like this:
    _______________________________________________________________________
   | | Dark shadows         |                                              |
   | |----------------------|                                              |
   | | Light shadows        |        C h a n g e   p a l e t t e           |
   | |----------------------|                                              |
   | | Background           |       .----------------------------.         |
   | |----------------------|       |  E  q  u  a  l  i  z  e  r |         |
   | | Equalizer 1 / Marker |       |                            |         |
   | |----------------------|       |                            |         |
   | | Equalizer 2          |       |                            |         |
   | |----------------------|       |                            |         |
   | | Equalizer 3          |       |                            |         |
   | |----------------------|       |____________________________|         |
   | | Equalizer 4          |           .--------------.                   |
   | |----------------------|           | Memory free: |                   |
   | | Text                 |           | Chip:        |                   |
   | `----------------------'           | Fast:        |                   |
   | .--------. .-----.                 `--------------'                   |
   | |@{" Change " LINK "How you change the palette"}| |     |                                                    |
   | `--------' `-----'                                                    |
