   | | Save settings |                                                     |
   | `---------------'                                                     |
   |-----------------------------------------------------------------------|
   |@{"                E x i t   t o  m a i n   s c r e e n                   " LINK "Main screen"}|
   `-----------------------------------------------------------------------'

   @{B}Dark shadow etc @{UB}- Change witch thing you should change when you press
                     the change button.
   @{B}Change          @{UB}- You will type in a number between 0-9 and A-F,
                     it will change the colours.
   @{B}Reset settings  @{UB}- It will turn the settings back to normal.
   @{B}Save settings   @{UB}- It will save the settings, NOT in UNREGISTERED
                     version.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "How you change the palette" "How you change the palette."
@TOC "MAINE"

   @{B}@{FG SHINE}=====»@{FG TEXT} How you change the palette. @{FG SHINE}«=====@{FG TEXT}@{UB}

   When you clicked on Change you must type in three hexdecimal characters.
   Hexdecimal characters is from 0 to 15.
   The character before the = is what you type in and the one after is what
   it will be for the program.
   0=0     8=8
   1=1     9=9
   2=2     A=10
   3=3     B=11
   4=4     C=12
   5=5     D=13
   6=6     E=14
   7=7     F=15
   You shall type in three hexdecimals. The first one is how much red it
   should be, the second is how much green it should be and the last one is
   how much blue it should be. 0=Nothing F=Full. That way F00 will become a
   red colour, 0F0 will become a green colour and 00F will become a blue
   character. You can combine them to get all different colour. For example
   000=Black bacause there is nothing of the colours, FFF=White because
   there is full of the three colours and 0FF will be yellow bacause when
   you mix green and blue you get yellow. I hope that you have understand
   this.

@ENDNODE

