@NODE "History" "The history of WonderWare-ModulePlayer."
@TOC "MAINS"

   @{B}@{FG SHINE}=====»@{FG TEXT} The history of WonderWare-ModulePlayer. @{FG SHINE}«=====@{FG TEXT}@{UB}

   @{B}V0.1 @{FG SHINE}1996-??-??@{FG TEXT}@{UB}
   First version. Wasn`t released. You can load 1 module in the memory.

   @{B}V0.2 @{FG SHINE}1996-??-??@{FG TEXT}@{UB}
   Fixed a bug when loading modules..

   @{B}V0.3 @{FG SHINE}1996-??-??@{FG TEXT}@{UB}
   Made the equalizer.

   @{B}V0.4 @{FG SHINE}1996-??-??@{FG TEXT}@{UB}
   The program bugs out if you load a MED module, I think I fixed it, but I
   am not sure. I haven`t fixed so you can play MED modules, but I will.

   @{B}V0.5 @{FG SHINE}1996-??-??@{FG TEXT}@{UB}
   The equalizer had a bug that made the fourth channel moved after the
   second channel. A stupid misstake.

   @{B}V0.6-V0.9@{UB}
   I skipped these versions because it was some big changes to version 1,0

   @{B}V0.3 @{FG SHINE}1996-??-??@{FG TEXT}@{UB}
   Fixed so you can load 13 modules in the memory. I also made a about
   screen and an registrations screen. On the registration screen can you
   print out the orderform if you have a printer. The program locks if you
   take print and you no printer is ready to print. I shall try to fix that.

   @{B}V1.0 @{FG SHINE}1996-??-??@{FG TEXT}@{UB}
   Fixed so the music wont stop if you load a module.

   @{B}V1.2-V1.7@{UB}
   I skipped these versions bacause the HD crasch. When I rewrote the
   program I jumped over some versions.

   @{B}V1.8 @{FG SHINE}1996-12-29@{FG TEXT}@{UB}
   My HD crasched. EVERYTHING vanished. So i had to rewrite this program
   from scratch. It was improved a little. Nicer looks. Now stores 16
   modules in the memory. The programs size has been reduced.
   But all wasn`t good. I haven`t fixed the about or registration screen
   yet, but i will as soon I have time. I haven`t released it yet because I
   want to fix some things first. But it will be released.

   @{B}V1,9 @{FG SHINE}1997-01-04@{FG TEXT}@{UB}
   First release.
   I`ve fixed so you can change the colours in the program and then when you
   exit it will be saved to a prefs file. I`ve fixed the about and
   registration screens. I`ve fixed so the program saves the modules that
   you have loaded and the next time you will start the program it will load
   the modules for you. I have also made so you can play MED modules. I
   fixed a bug that made the program lock.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HARD-DISK" "ALL HARD-DISK USERS SHOULD READ THIS."
@TOC "MAINE"

   @{B}@{FG SHINE}=====»@{FG TEXT} ALL HARD-DISK USERS SHOULD READ THIS. @{FG SHINE}«=====@{FG TEXT}@{UB}

   If you have an Hard-Disk and don`t have backups of programs and games,
   DO IT!!!!!!!! When i got a 2,1GB Hard-Disk and plugged it in, I
   accidentaly started HDSetup and that creepy program overwrote my
   partitions and the 420MB harddisk was empty... All my work in AMOS,
   some games and programs that I didn`t had backups of was gone for ever.
   WonderWare-ModulePlayer is the first program that I have rewritten to
   it`s original shape and then I have modified it to be as good as posible.

   My last word to ALL harddisk users, @{FG SHINE}GET A BACKUP PROGRAM OR JUST COPY
   THE FILES TO SOME DISKS.@{FG TEXT}

@ENDNODE

